## Overview

This project builds a phishing URL detection system using supervised machine learning. The pipeline covers:
- Feature engineering on URL structure, HTML content, and domain characteristics
- Training and hyperparameter tuning of Random Forest and XGBoost
- Cross-dataset generalization testing
- SHAP-based model explainability
- Inference speed and model size comparison

---

## Datasets

| Dataset | Size | Source | Labels |
|---|---|---|---|
| **PhiUSIIL** | 235,795 URLs | [UCI ML Repository](https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/967/phiusiil+phishing+url+dataset) | 0 = Legitimate, 1 = Phishing |
| **dataset_phishing** | 11,430 URLs | [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/shashwatwork/web-page-phishing-detection-dataset) | legitimate / phishing |

> ️ Datasets are not included in this repo due to size. Download from the links above and place in your working directory.

